column1: #mapping_set_title: MP to HPO mappings for COVID related phenotypes

#mapping_set_description: Set consists of phenotype terms in MP and HPO related to symptoms of COVID-19. COVID-19 symptoms were identified from the literature and reliable websites. The source for each symptom is listed in the "other" field. Use of SSSOM terms: skos:exactMatch - terms have the same meaning except that MP term is not limited to human; skos:broadMatch ontology term would be a parent to the symptom or MP term would be a parent to HPO term; skos:narrowMatch - ignoring species limit MP term would be a child of the HPO term; skos:closeMatch terms are almost skos:exactMatch but there is a subtle distinction; skos:relatedMatch - terms are similar but would not have a parent/child relation in an ontology. Cut off for skos:broadMatch was based on the term having just subtypes of the phenotype, i.e. if it matches the general phenotype but doesn't specify the location then it got a skos:broadMatch mapping, but if the phenotype was for a specific cell type and the closest match was just for the general tissue no mapping was made. Source for COVID symptoms are listed in the comment column.

MP has a separate term for "hyperglycemia" (MP:0001559) that has as part of the definition "generally refers to a pathological state". The HPO term Hyperglycemia is defined as "An increased concentration of glucose in the blood." making it a better match to the MP term "increased circulating glucose level" defined as "greater than the normal concentration in the blood of this major monosaccharide of the body; it is an important energy source"
